<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-05T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00/470: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-05T19:00:00-04:00">September 5, 1930—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 5—6:45 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>120. Foreign Office confirms that President has on account of ill health
                            delegated his authority to the Vice President and that martial law is
                            expected shortly to be declared.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>